    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the inherent constraint of the ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol and is consistent with regulatory practice for this device class. All three pre-specified QoI acceptance criteria are satisfied (percent difference < 10%, E/uval < 1.96). The assessment team judges the overall credibility sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design. Decision: Accepted with acknowledgement of test-condition limitation.",
